\b \cf3 \cb4 \strokec5 Dandiya Raas
\b0  is the traditional \strokec6 folk dance\strokec5  form of \strokec6 Gujarat\strokec5  & \strokec6 Rajasthan\strokec5  \strokec6 India\strokec5 , and is associated with scenes of \strokec6 Holi\strokec5 , and \strokec6 lila\strokec5  of \strokec6 Krishna\strokec5  and \strokec6 Radha\strokec5  at \strokec6 Vrindavan\strokec5 . Along with \strokec6 Garba\strokec5 , it is the featured \strokec6 dance\strokec5  of \strokec6 Navratri\strokec5  evenings in \strokec6 Western India\strokec5 . During \strokec6 Navratri\strokec5  festival, in most of the cities of \strokec6 Gujarat\strokec5  & \strokec6 Rajasthan\strokec5  people gather and perform \strokec6 Garba\strokec5  dance - an event that is becoming increasingly popular in countries with large Gujarati-speaking communities around the world, such as Canada, the United States and the United Kingdom.\
