\b \cf3 \strokec2 Etymology
\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec5 The word "Raas" comes from the \strokec6 Sanskrit\strokec5  word "\strokec6 Rasa\strokec5 ". The origins of Raas can be traced to ancient times. \strokec6 Lord Krishna\strokec5  performed \strokec6 Rasa lila\strokec5 " (\strokec7 Lila\strokec5  means Lord Krishna's playful dance. The word "Laika" also refers to things that God does that we fully understand).\
