\b \cf3 \strokec2 Forms of Raas
\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\sa140\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec5 There are several forms of Raas, but "Dandiya Raas", performed during \strokec6 Navaratri\strokec5  in \strokec6 Gujarat\strokec5  is the most popular form. Other forms of Raas include Dang Lila from \strokec6 Rajasthan\strokec5  where only one large stick is used, and "\strokec6 Rasa lila\strokec5 " from \strokec6 North India\strokec5 . Raas Lila and Dandiya Raas are similar. Some even consider "\strokec6 Garba\strokec5 " as a form of Raas, namely "Raas Garba".\
In Dandiya Raas men and women dance in two circles, with sticks in their hands.\
