\b \cf3 \strokec2 History
\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\sa140\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec5 The Dandiya Raas dance originated as devotional Garba dances, which were performed in Goddess Durga\'92s honor. This dance form is actually the staging of a mock-fight between Goddess Durga and Mahishasura, the mighty demon-king. This dance is also nicknamed \'91The Sword Dance\'92. The sticks of the dance represent the sword of Goddess Durga.\
The origin of these dances can be traced back to the life of Lord Krishna. Today, Raas is not only an important part of Navaratri in Gujarat but extends itself to other festivals related to harvest and crops as well.\
